The paper deals with recommending points of interest (POIs) in location-based social networks (LBSNs), which involves information retrieval (IR) and social networks (SOC). The proposed algorithm uses collaborative ranking (LG) and regularization techniques, which are common in machine learning (LG) and databases (DB). The paper also mentions the use of geographical influence, which could fall under the sub-category of spatial information (SI).
